Add a public function called HasValue to Collections.calr that creates a list and checks if it contains a specific value. It takes i32 parameter value and returns bool.

Use this exact Calor contains check syntax:
§F{f001:HasValue:pub}
  §I{i32:value}
  §O{bool}
  §LIST{items:i32}
    10
    20
    30
  §/LIST{items}
  §R §HAS{items} value
§/F{f001}

The §HAS{collection} value syntax checks if the collection contains the value:
- Returns true if found, false otherwise
- Works with List, HashSet, Dictionary (checks keys)
